techmeme.title: MrBeast joins an investor group led by Employer.com founder Jesse Tinsley in an all-cash bid to acquire TikTok US operations; several groups have shown interest (Alexandra S. Levine/Bloomberg)
OpenAI, SoftBank, and Oracle announce The Stargate Project, a JV to invest in US AI infrastructure, committing $100B now and up to $500B in the next four years (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
Nielsen: Netflix captured 8.5% of all US streaming viewership in December 2024, its highest share since July 2023, in part due to NFL games; YouTube had 11.1% (Drew Lerner/Awful Announcing)
Crypto.com launches its institutional exchange service for US customers; it had closed the service in June 2023 due to "limited demand" (MK Manoylov/The Block)
Tencent unveils Hunyuan3D 2.0, an AI system that turns single images or text prompts into 3D models in seconds, and open sources it on HuggingFace and GitHub (Michael Nuñez/VentureBeat)
